enhanced_by.reason: The addAll method internally uses the add method to add each element from the collection, making it a direct dependency for setting up the test.
Both methods require a SortedBag instance to be initialized, which can be reused in setting up the test environment.
The containsAll method can be used to verify that all elements added by addAll are present in the bag, providing a direct assertion for the test.
The removeAll method can be used to remove the added elements and verify that the bag is back to its original state, ensuring the test is properly cleaned up.
